El componente depublicidad para teleSUR esta basado en el componente 
"Lite Video Ads With Posters" ( http://activeden.net/item/lite-video-ads-with-posters/310612 )

Se modificó para poder recibir como parámetros flashvars/QueryString la configuración
de video y poster. (Técnicamente, se le puede pasar toda la configuración limitada
a sólo un elemento de video)

Aún puede recibir el parametro xmlpath para indicar un xml que contiene la configuración

----
Componente original
----
Lite Video Ads with Posters

version: v.1.0
author:  codelite
----

If you want o use your method of embending just make sure the template.xml is in the same folder with the 
swf movieclip, or set the 'xmlpath' flashvar to what path the template.xml has.


Make sure you set the size of the swf to match the size of the image you are using as background



[ CUSTOMIZATION ]

In the [3]Deploy folder the customization file is 'template.xml'



<background_color>

This is the color of component's background.



<normal_button_color>

The color of the button when mouse is not over it



<hoover_button_color>

The color of the button when mouse is over it


<transition_effect>

If the component is using the transition effect at the end of the movie: set false /true



<restart_video_first_time_sound_on>

#false: onece you press the sound button on the video keeps playing with sound on
#true:  the first time the 'sound on' is pressed the video will restart with sound on ( it will never restart on second use and further)



<list>

This list  works with a singe item up to as many items you want.

If you have more than one video the list will randomly pick one to show at every page loading



<item>
	
The setup of the item


	<poster>  the path to the image poster

	<video>   the path to the video


		  Support for normal videos and youtube videos


		  If you are using an youtube video make sure the format of the link is as follows

		  http://www.youtube.com/v/video_id


	<video_width>  the width of the video

	<video_height> the height of the video
	
	<video_position_x> the X position of the movie on the stage

	<video_position_y> the Y position of the stage

	<sound_position> the sound button position

			top_left / top_right / top_middle
                        bottom_left / bottom_right / bottom_middle


	<replay_position> the replay button position	

			top_left / top_right / top_middle
                        bottom_left / bottom_right / bottom_middle	
		

	<transition> the type of the transition effect ( if activated )
 
		     from 1- 10 or write 'random'


	<link> the external link

	       #window - how the links open: _parent ( same page )
					     _blank  ( new page /tab )




